{"source_key":"sha256-f88bd5c54ac5fbbfc982c6d403b2565f","record_index":459,"record_hash":"sha256:b987dc713ff9faac2e9592b37dd3b35df981d4581f80ef1ec25d231b70a8ad45","timestamp":"2026-05-24T14:43:30.463Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"I reviewed it. No edits made.\\n\\n**High-Signal Issues**\\n1. **The doc says both “ready” and “not ready.”**  \\n   [agent-trail.md](</Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 Active/agent-session-capture/agent-trail.md:256>) says don’t implement until publication/permissions are clearer, but [line 579](</Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 Active/agent-session-capture/agent-trail.md:579>) says no major blockers. Pick one. For MVP, I’d say: build may start for public repos/public metadata only.\\n\\n2. **Publication boundary is still the one real ambiguity.**  \\n   If public repo + public `refs/meta/main` means “safe to render on demand,” say that explicitly. Otherwise an implementation agent may invent an approval flow.\\n\\n3. **`but-agentlog` does not currently expose the API the doc implies.**  \\n   The doc says Forge should call read/query/projection primitives, but [lib.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/lib.rs:1) only exports CLI-shaped entry points; the useful read functions are `pub(crate)`. MVP probably needs a tiny public library API, not shelling out to `but`.\\n\\n4. **There are stale/conflicting breadcrumbs.**  \\n   [line 306](</Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 Active/agent-session-capture/agent-trail.md:306>) still says `PR/branch/change`, but change lookup is out for MVP. [line 284](</Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 Active/agent-session-capture/agent-trail.md:284>) mentions configured metadata remotes, while [line 330](</Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 Active/agent-session-capture/agent-trail.md:330>) says no config yet.\\n\\n5. **Snapshot identity needs deterministic rules.**  \\n   “PR number + metadata ref OID + selected session/turn keys” is good, but add: sorted keys, deduped sessions, review match outranks branch match, stable hash/id from normalized tuple.\\n\\n6. **Redaction wording needs reconciliation.**  \\n   “No extra public redaction” is fine, but then the acceptance bar should say Agent Trail only displays `but-agentlog` redacted/readout data, hidden/system/developer records must be absent, and raw provider ids/local paths must not appear through the chosen API.\\n\\n7. **Failure states need minimum expected behavior.**  \\n   Add explicit MVP states for: invalid URL, public PR not found, fork PR unsupported, metadata ref missing, no matching sessions, GitHub API rate-limited, fetch/read error.\\n\\n**Minimum Acceptance Criteria To Add**\\n- URL replacement route parses `/:owner/:repo/pull/:number`.\\n- Server checks the GitHub repo/PR is publicly readable.\\n- First request initializes a bare/cache repo; later requests refetch.\\n- Server fetches only `refs/meta/main` for MVP.\\n- Lookup searches `gitbutler-review:<pr>` and `ref:refs/heads/<head-branch>`.\\n- Results dedupe sessions/turns and rank review matches above branch-only matches.\\n- Snapshot has stable id from PR number, metadata OID, selected session/turn keys.\\n- Page shows PR identity, snapshot metadata/OID, sessions list, match reasons, turn timeline, expandable records.\\n- No fork PR support in v1; show a clear unsupported state.\\n- No extra public redaction pass; use only baseline `but-agentlog` redacted output.\\n- Tests cover URL parsing, target-key normalization, review+branch dedupe/ranking, missing metadata, and no matching sessions.\\n\\n**Must-Ask Before Building**\\n1. For public v1, does **public repo + public `refs/meta/main`** authorize on-demand rendering with no extra owner approval?  \\n   My pick: **yes**. It’s already public metadata; URL replacement is just a viewer.\\n\\n2. Is the MVP allowed to modify `but-agentlog` to expose a small public read/projection API for Forge?  \\n   My pick: **yes**. Shelling out to `but agentlog` from the server would be a crappy foundation.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T14:43:30.463Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user"}}}